Review: going into this I was prepared to have some sort of epiphany, or at least cry a little. but for the most part it was just a movie. a breathtakingly beautiful and imaginative movie, of course, but one that I didn’t really connect with on the level I had hoped
criticisms to be made for sure, but for the most part I really enjoyed this. very creative and funny! I just still can’t believe they chose that fuckass Rae Dunn font

mixed feelings about this one. Frances is a fantastic actress but I think this would’ve come across as much more authentic without her there. like great acting only does so much when you’re very keenly aware that it’s an act. great visuals though
this made me realize I need more fun silly whimsical cinema in my life. I had the best time watching this AND it was less than two hours which my real fans will know is the gold standard

Review: haven’t seen this since it was in theaters. I knew it was bad but holy fuck
when they did the Big Reveal and he’s typing all that nonsense on the laptop that’s when I decided this couldn’t be more than 3 stars
least scary horror movie of all time. the LSHMOAT if you will. kind of insane that they even billed it as horror actually
this felt like 3 hours but when it comes to picking a Christmas movie that no one’s seen before we could’ve done a lot worse
